TO MAKE THE VEGETABLE STOCK: In a medium (8- to 12-quart [7.6- to l1.4-L]) stockpot, bring the water, carrot, celery, onion, and parsley to a boil. Reduce the heat to low, cover the stockpot, and cook for 30 to 40 minutes. Strain the stock into another bowl or container and discard the vegetables. 3. Strain the stock into another bowl or container and discard the vegetables.